     Help     Sandbox     Recent Changes                          in: Males, Members of the Alliance, European individuals, Gellert Grindelwald's Paris rally participants         English     Deutsch   Deutsch   Español   Français   Polski               Nagel              View source                         History                         Talk (0)                                         Nagel   Biographical information  Born Before 1927    Physical information  Species Human   Gender Male    Affiliation  Loyalty Gellert GrindelwaldThe AllianceGellert Grindelwald's acolytes   [Source]  Nagel was a wizard who lived during the early 20th century. He was a member of Gellert Grindelwald's Alliance, and was among the dark wizard's foremost acolytes.[1]  Contents  1 Biography 2 Magical abilities and skills 3 Etymology 4 Behind the scenes 5 Appearances 6 Notes and references   Biography    Nagel talking with Grindelwald   Nagel joined Gellert Grindelwald at some point prior to 1927, and became one of Grindelwald's seven trusted acolytes. Under Grindelwald's orders, Nagel was told to visit the Circus Arcanus' performance, so as to keep an eye on the Obscurial Credence Barebone.[2]  Magical abilities and skills Apparition: Nagel was accomplished in apparition, as he was able to Disapparate successfully away from the Lestrange Mausoleum after passing through Grindelwald's circle of allegiance. Etymology In Swedish, Norwegian, German and Dutch, "nagel" means "nail". Behind the scenes Nagel is portrayed by Claudius Peters in the second instalment of the Fantastic Beasts film series. In The Art of Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald, Nagel's early portrayal resembled Percival Graves. In an early draft of the the storyboard, Nagel was meant to meet up with Credence in the bird market. Appearances The Harry Potter Wiki has 2 images related to Nagel. Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald - The Original Screenplay (First appearance) Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald The Archive of Magic: The Film Wizardry of Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald Pottermore (Mentioned only) Wizarding World (Mentioned only) Notes and references   ↑ Full Character Profiles from The Leaky Cauldron  ↑ Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald - The Original Screenplay     The Alliance   Leader  Gellert Grindelwald     Acolytes  Abernathy | Credence Barebone (defected) | Carrow | Queenie Goldstein (defected) | Krafft | Krall (deceased) | MacDuff | Nagel | Vinda Rosier | Zabini   Followers  Cassius Bell | Gunnar Grimmson | Helmut | Karl | Anton Vogel | Henrietta Fischer   Headquarters  Unidentified home | Nurmengard             Categories         Categories:   Males    Members of the Alliance    European individuals    Gellert Grindelwald's Paris rally participants             Languages      Deutsch Deutsch Español Français Polski      *Disclosure: Some of the links above are affiliate links, meaning, at no additional cost to you, Fandom will earn a commission if you click through and make a purchase. Community content is available under CC-BY-SA unless otherwise noted.             Advertisement     Fan Feed        More Harry Potter Wiki     1 Sirius Black     2 Hufflepuff     3 Ravenclaw                           Explore Wikis            Universal Conquest Wiki        Let's Go Luna! Wiki        Club 57 Wiki                              Explore properties          Fandom               Cortex RPG               Muthead               Futhead               Fanatical          Follow Us                                Overview          What is Fandom?               About               Careers               Press               Contact               Terms of Use               Privacy Policy               Global Sitemap               Local Sitemap            Community          Community Central               Support               Help               Do Not Sell My Info          Advertise          Media Kit               Fandomatic               Con